 yoga is a general term for practices that modify yoga poses so they can be done while seated in a chair.";i:1;s:179:"These modifications make yoga accessible to people who cannot stand lack the mobility to move easily from standing to seated to supine positions or want a quick break from office.";i:2;s:24:"Seated chair yoga poses.";i:3;s:154:"Begin each posture seated on a chair with your spine long and straight both feet flat on the floor letting your hands rest on top of your knees or thighs.";i:4;s:23:"Mountain pose Tadasana.";i:5;s:93:"Take a deep breath and on an exhale root your bodyweight into the chair using your sit bones.";i:6;s:47:"Its perfect for people who sit for a long time.";i:7;s:81:"This pose opens the hip joint increases hip flexibility and stretches the thighs.";i:8;s:93:"After finishing 5 yoga chair poses keep seated and close your eyes for a 5-minute meditation.";i:9;s:98:"These 5 poses will benefit yoga followers in a chair and help you to achieve yoga practice easily.";i:10;s:141:"Sitting on a chair with your spine straight and feet flat on the floor hinge forward from the hips and let your torso fold between your legs.";i:11;s:94:"When you can no longer hinge any further round your spine and drop your head toward the floor.";i:12;s:68:"Most positions begin using the same seated position called Sit tall.";i:13;s:210:"Sit in a chair with feet planted firmly on the floor Back straight to elongate your spine Hands may be at your sides or on your legs tips Move slowly through each pose holding each pose for 3 to 5 slow breaths.";i:14;s:85:"If a pose is challenging pause and start again when your breathing returns to normal.";i:15;s:108:"Chair Yoga Poses also decreases the risk of serious ailments such as diabetes heart disease and even cancer.";i:16;s:74:"A sedentary lifestyle also results in increased anxiety and stress levels.";i:17;s:156:"If you do not take steps to become more physically active and spend lesser time sitting down you may end up with health issues that can last for a lifetime.";i:18;s:44:"Sit on a chair with your feet on the ground.";i:19;s:48:"Place your feet about as wide as the chair seat.";i:20;s:106:"With your torso upright reach your hands down by the sides of the chair for seated Tadasana Mountain Pose.";i:21;s:26:"Inhale and lift your arms.";i:22;s:121:"Exhale and fold forward by bringing your torso closer to your thighs into a seated Uttanasana Standing Forward Bend Pose.";i:23;s:51:"You can rest your hands on the chair legs floor or.";i:24;s:117:"Starting seated in neutral in a chair wrap your right thigh over your left thigh you can hook your right foot around.";i:25;s:114:"Stretch your arms out straight in front of you then cross your left arm over your right arm bend both arms at the.";i:26;s:58:"Roll the shoulders back and down while keeping your spine.";i:27;s:107:"Chair yoga is a wonderful practice for every body suitable for beginners and seniorsFULL CHAIR YOGA COURSE.";i:28;s:96:"Sit on the floor in front of your chair with your legs extended in front of you under the chair.";i:29;s:76:"Here experts tell us what exactly chair yoga is and how to start a practice.";i:30;s:40:"Seated forward bend with chair benefits.";i:31;s:55:"Chair yoga is simply adapting yoga asanas with a chair.";i:32;s:30:"At least in the literal sense.";i:33;s:19:"SITTING IN A CHAIR.";i:34;s:109:"This pose is as good as any other pose and normally used when none of the other ones are physically possible.";i:35;s:57:"However this pose may be too comfortable so remain alert.";i:36;s:68:"Choose a good firm chair with a straight back to support your spine.";i:37;s:82:"Sit in a chair placing both feet flat on the floor and keeping the spine straight.";i:38;s:73:"This yoga practice is designed for those seated in a wheelchair or chair.";i:39;s:63:"A wonderful and refreshing practice to align the mind and body.";i:40;s:120:"Below is a list of basic chair yoga poses which are ancient yoga poses that have been adapted to practice using a chair.";i:41;s:149:"These chair yoga poses could be used in your classroom homeschool or in a small space for transitions movement breaks or for introducing a new topic.";i:42;s:89:"The postures serve as an inspiration guide but please encourage the childrens creativity.";i:43;s:50:"Find all these chair yoga poses in our Chair Yoga.";i:44;s:126:"To do this as you sit focus on lengthening the center of your spine up from your sitting bones through the crown of your head.";i:45;s:101:"Notice how long you can maintain this feeling of inner lift before you begin to sag and lose support.";i:46;s:56:"Then try to re-establish the movement again for a while.";i:47;s:17:"This is cow pose.";i:48;s:73:"Repeat this motion several times inhaling into cat and exhaling into cow.";i:49;s:87:"Place your left hand on your right knee and your right arm over the back of your chair.";i:50;s:64:"Turn to look over your right shoulder and hold for four breaths.";i:51;s:77:"On the inhale feel your spine lengthen and on the exhale feel a deeper twist.";i:52;s:51:"Exhale back to center and repeat on the other side.";i:53;s:32:"Yoga chair poses and stretching.";i:54;s:122:"Woman sitting on chair and stretching to touch her toes Koldunov Getty Images You know you need to sit less and move more.";i:55;s:67:"But what if at the very least you could move while you were seated.";i:56;s:18:"It is a wise idea.";i:57;s:47:"When you stretch or move frequently throughout.";i:58;s:90:"Read more about the exercises below for a closer look at these essential chair yoga poses.";i:59;s:76:"Begin in a seated position facing forward with your arms down by your sides.";i:60;s:78:"Take a long deep breath in and slowly stretch your arms upward to the ceiling.";i:61;s:72:"Start this pose sitting on the front half of your chair with a straight.";i:62;s:73:"Chair yoga is a form of yoga that has been adapted from traditional yoga.";i:63;s:140:"Typically chair yoga is practiced sitting on a chair or using a chair for support yet still allows for twists stretches and minor backbends.";i:64;s:127:"Chair yoga is ideal for those who might not be able to take part in traditional yoga due to mobility restrictions an injury or.";i:65;s:115:"The majority of yoga poses in a chair yoga sequence on the other hand take place from a seated position in a chair.";i:66;s:178:"Depending on the mobility of the class a yoga teacher might include a pose or two that involves standing up perhaps using stabilizing hands on the chair to aid and train balance.";i:67;s:154:"Such is the popularity of this form of yoga nowadays that it is also being included in certain 200-hour yoga teacher training programs in Nepal and India.";i:68;s:93:"A number of yoga schools across the globe also include chair yoga in their teaching programs.";i:69;s:97:"In short the importance of chair yoga can be described better through practice rather than words.";}}